From: Andrew Morton <akpm@linux-foundation.org>
Date: Mon, 18 May 2026 18:15:39 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] mm-swap-merge-zeromap-into-swap-table-fix

swap_cluster_alloc_table(): remove unused local `ret'

Cc: Kairui Song <kasong@tencent.com>
Signed-off-by: Andrew Morton <akpm@linux-foundation.org>
---
 mm/swapfile.c | 1 -
 1 file changed, 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/mm/swapfile.c b/mm/swapfile.c
index ef48cf2a8d967..58059e44b7ff3 100644
--- a/mm/swapfile.c
+++ b/mm/swapfile.c
@@ -450,7 +450,6 @@ static int swap_cluster_alloc_table(struct swap_cluster_info *ci, gfp_t gfp)
 {
 	struct swap_table *table = NULL;
 	struct folio *folio;
-	int ret = 0;
 
 	/* The cluster must be empty and not on any list during allocation. */
 	VM_WARN_ON_ONCE(ci->flags || !cluster_is_empty(ci));
-- 
2.47.3

